The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Aug. 18: Indias forex reserves dropped by $346 million to $228.996 billion for the week ended August 10. It shot up by $3.9 billion to $229.342 billion in the previous week. According to figures released by the Reserve Bank, foreign currency assets (FCA) decreased by $335 million to $221.653 billion. FCAs in dollars include the effect of revaluation of non-US currencies such as euro, sterling and yen held in reserves.

 Calcutta, Aug. 18: Designing and consultancy firm Mecon Ltds order book for the current fiscal has reached Rs 400-crore mark. The company has bagged contracts for expansion of all SAIL plants. It is also eyeing contracts for the plants to be set up by private players like the Jindals and the Mittals.

 Mumbai, Aug. 18: Kumar Mangalam Birla has been re-appointed director of Hindalco Industries. Shareholders also approved the re- appointment of E.B. Desai and A.K. Agarwala as directors.




